On July 4, 2023, Vice President Harris visited Los Angeles Fire Station 39 in Van Nuys, California to express gratitude for the work of firefighters. She shared a personal connection as her husband's brother recently retired as a firefighter. Harris acknowledged the important role firefighters play in dealing with extreme weather conditions like fires and floods, as well as the medical emergencies they respond to. She recognized the sacrifices they make and mentioned efforts to provide more benefits for federal firefighters. Harris emphasized the need for a comprehensive emergency response to extreme weather conditions, particularly wildfires. She praised the station for being a model for the rest of the country and thanked the firefighters for their dedication and noble work. The Vice President brought pies as a token of appreciation and encouraged the firefighters to take some time to rest.